title: normoandrogenic woman, biological rep1
source_name_ch1: subcutaneous adipose tissue from fat biopsy
growth_protocol_ch1: Approximately 0.5-1g of freshly isolated SC adipose was obtained through a 1 cm lower abdominal incision and was washed with DMEM and then digested at 37°C in DMEM containing 0.075% collagenase for 45-60 min on a shaker. Adipocytes (floating cells) were separated from pellets by centrifugation (800×g, 10 min). Pellets containing stromal-vascular fraction were resuspended in DMEM/5% fetal calf serum (FCS), filtered through 150-mm mesh and washed with DMEM/10% FCS. Cells were plated in 60 mm dishes containing DMEM/10% FCS, 0.05 U/ml penicillin, 0.05 mg/ml streptomycin, 1.25 mg/ml fungizone and cultured at 37°C for 1-2 weeks until cells reached confluency
extract_protocol_ch1: Total cellular RNA was isolated from 2 x 10 cm dishes of SC abdominal ASCs using RNeasy mini kit (Qiagen, Carlsbad, CA) according to the manufacturer’s protocol.
label_protocol_ch1: Samples were enzymatically fragmented and biotinylated using the WT Terminal Labeling Kit (Affymetrix)
hyb_protocol: Hybridization was performed using Affymetrix GeneChip Hybridization Wash and Stain kit.
data_processing: Data were processed using Expression Console
